{
  "style": "APA",
  "texts": [
    "Extractive methods generate summaries by selecting sentences directly from the original document, resulting in summaries that are more accurate and semantically consistent but may lack coherence.",
    "In contrast, abstractive methods generate summaries based on an understanding of the text, rather than extracting sentences directly from the original document.",
    "Therefore, summaries produced by this approach are typically more coherent and better aligned with human reading preferences (El-Kassas et al., 2021; Ghadimi & Beigy, 2022).",
    "In this paper, we focus on abstractive summarization.",
    "The source article is from the paper (Sunakawa et al., 2024) and (Fu et al., 2020)."
  ],
